---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Corporate Events" description="Wine-focused team building and client entertainment for Bay Area companies. Sommelier-led experiences designed for the modern workplace.">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <p class="text-amber-600 font-medium tracking-wider uppercase text-sm mb-3">Services</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-6">Corporate Wine Events</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-12 max-w-2xl">
      Elevate your next team offsite, client dinner, or holiday party with a sommelier-guided wine experience that's as engaging as it is memorable.
    </p>

    <div class="prose prose-stone max-w-none">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900">Why Wine for Team Building?</h2>
      <p>Wine tastings create a uniquely effective environment for corporate gatherings. Unlike ropes courses or escape rooms, wine tasting is inherently social, intellectually stimulating, and inclusive across all fitness levels and personality types. Introverts and extroverts alike engage naturally when there's a glass in hand and a story being told.</p>

      <p>The sensory vocabulary required to describe wine — acidity, tannin, fruit character, finish — gives colleagues a shared language and a level playing field. Your CEO and your newest intern are equally novice (or expert) when it comes to identifying whether they're tasting Malbec or Merlot.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10">Event Formats</h2>

      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-6">Team Tasting (10–25 people)</h3>
      <p>A guided tasting of 5–6 wines with interactive elements. I break large groups into tasting teams, introduce friendly competition (blind tasting rounds, aroma identification challenges), and keep the energy high. Perfect for team offsites, all-hands celebrations, or Friday afternoon wind-downs.</p>

      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-6">Client Entertainment (6–12 people)</h3>
      <p>A more refined, intimate experience designed to impress. I work with you to select wines that align with your brand's values or your client's known preferences. The pacing is relaxed, the wines are premium, and the conversation flows naturally. I can coordinate with caterers to provide complementary food pairings.</p>

      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-6">Conference or Large Event (25–50 people)</h3>
      <p>Multiple tasting stations, each featuring a different region or theme. Guests circulate freely, sampling wines and engaging with educational materials at each station. I provide printed tasting cards, QR codes linking to deeper content, and optional gamification (passport stamps, leaderboard for correct blind guesses).</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10">What's Included</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Pre-event consultation to customize the experience for your team</li>
        <li>All wines, glassware, and printed materials</li>
        <li>Professional sommelier guidance throughout the event</li>
        <li>Post-event wine list with purchasing recommendations for attendees</li>
        <li>Optional: coordinated catering recommendations or food pairing menu design</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10">Pricing</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Format</th><th>Group Size</th><th>Duration</th><th>Starting At</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Team Tasting</td><td>10–25</td><td>1.5–2 hrs</td><td>$1,200</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Client Entertainment</td><td>6–12</td><td>2–2.5 hrs</td><td>$1,500</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Conference Stations</td><td>25–50</td><td>2–3 hrs</td><td>$2,500</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="text-sm text-stone-500">All prices include wines and materials. Travel within the Bay Area included. Larger groups and multi-session packages available upon request.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10">Companies I've Worked With</h2>
      <p>I've hosted wine events for teams at technology companies, law firms, financial services firms, and startups across Silicon Valley and San Francisco. While I respect client confidentiality, I'm happy to share references upon request.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 bg-amber-50 rounded-xl p-8 text-center">
      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Plan your next event</h3>
      <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">I recommend 4+ weeks lead time for corporate events to ensure optimal wine sourcing and logistics.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="bg-amber-600 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-amber-700 transition-colors inline-block">Contact Me</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
